Hey @jdalton we discussed this previously last spring when I was working on [lodash-modularize](https://github.com/megawac/lodash-modularize) over gitter. It would be nice if it were possible to create lodash compatible wrapper -- lazy functionality and all.

Currently the behavior can be approximated using mixin and calling the `LodashWrapper` [through a wrapper](https://github.com/megawac/lodash-modularize/blob/master/templates/chain-build.tpl) (wrapper required as `runInContext` also is not in the modular build) similar to as follows:

``` js
import lodash from 'lodash/chain/lodash';
import LodashWrapper from 'lodash/internal/LodashWrapper';

import create from 'lodash/object/create';
import mixin from 'lodash/utility/mixin';

function _(value) {
  if (!(this instanceof _)) {
    return new _(value);
  }
  LodashWrapper.call(this, value);
}
_.prototype = create(lodash.prototype);

mixin(_, {
  // lodash methods
}, true);
```

However, in the modular builds the lazy code is only about a quarter present, with some implementations of `chain` methods considering lazyWrappers. Also the `lazyWrapper` is included in the modular builds despite no decent way of using it.

---

I'd like a way to use lazy functionality with modular builds. Rather than exposing this through the `chaining` api I'd suggest it be accessible through the `flow` and `compose` APIs. This would make it easier for the end user (or transpiler ^^) as they would not have to spoof the lodash wrapper. Further, all of the chaining API features are can be easily written through `flow` or `compose`.

Along with this proposition I would suggest that the chaining api is no longer exposed in the modular build as its use is kind of impractical.

I realize this proposition would require significant refactoring as I expect it would require the chaining api to be implemented through `flow` and `compose`.

