Hello everyone,

I just wanted to ask, if you ever thought about implementing haskells scanl function. It works like a fusion of map and reduce in the way, that every returned value of the function is added to the result array and the last result is available in that function. An example implementation could look a little like this:

```
function scan(array, fn, seed, thisArg) {
  var accumulator = seed;
  var results = [];
  if (seed === undefined) {
    accumulator = _.head(array);
    array = _.tail(array);
  }
  results.push(accumulator);
  _.forEach(array, function (nextValue) {
    accumulator = fn.call(thisArg, accumulator, nextValue);
    results.push(accumulator);
  });
  return results;
};    
```

